propel.core.collections.lists

Class SortedList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractQueue<E>
        • java.util.PriorityQueue<T>
          • propel.core.collections.lists.SortedList<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.Queue<T>, ReifiedIterable<T>

    public class SortedList<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.util.PriorityQueue<T>
implements ReifiedIterable<T>
    A type-aware sorted list of comparable elements. This collection does not allow nulls to be inserted. Instantiate using e.g.: new SortedList<String>(){}; -OR- new SortedList<String>(String.class);
    See Also:
